history.content: 106a is exclusively a fall class, and 106b exclusively a spring class. There's a reasonable chance that 106B will be webcast 1.5 years from now, but I don't plan to be teaching it then and it's a long ways away. Also much of the value of 106B is in the labs/projects, and you won't be able to complete those away from berkeley.

Will c106a be offered next spring? Or is it exclusively a fall class? I am graduating next fall, and thus would not be able to take 106b if it is not offered in the spring. If 106a is not offered next spring, is there a way I could follow along with 106b (given that I took 106a next fall) while im not at berkeley? Thanks.
